      "style": "solid"
    },
    {
      "id": "p-intro-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "We've been living with a fundamental paradox in the digital age: the most beautiful documents are the hardest to work with. PDF, introduced in 1993, solved the problem of consistent presentation across devices. But in doing so, it created a new problemâ€”documents became frozen artifacts, difficult to edit, impossible for AI to understand properly, and frustrating to work with.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-intro-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Enter Nova, a new document format that promises to give us the best of all worlds: the beauty of PDF, the editability of modern tools like Notion, and the semantic structure that AI systems need to truly understand our content.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "h2-problem",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "The PDF Problem",
      "anchor": "problem",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-problem-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Ask anyone who works with documents regularly, and they'll have a PDF horror story. Maybe it's the contract that needed one small change but required recreating the entire document. Perhaps it's the research paper where AI couldn't properly extract the table data. Or the form that looked perfect on screen but printed incorrectly.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "quote-frustration",
      "type": "quote",
      "content": "We've spent 30 years creating billions of documents in a format that's fundamentally incompatible with the future we're building.",
      "author": "Dr. James Martinez",
      "source": "MIT Technology Review, 2024"
    },
    {
      "id": "p-problem-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "The problem isn't that PDF is bad at what it doesâ€”preserving exact visual appearance. The problem is that we need documents to do more than just look good. We need them to be editable, searchable, accessible, and most importantly in 2025, understandable by AI systems.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "callout-stat",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "info",
      "title": "By The Numbers",
      "icon": "ðŸ“Š",
      "content": "Over 2.5 trillion PDF files are created annually, but 78% of knowledge workers report frustration with PDF workflows, and AI systems achieve only 60-70% accuracy when extracting structured data from PDFs."
    },
    {
      "id": "h2-alternatives",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "The Alternatives Fall Short",
      "anchor": "alternatives",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-alt-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Frustrated by PDF's limitations, we've seen various alternatives emerge over the years:",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "layout-alternatives",
      "type": "layout",
      "columns": [
        {
          "width": "1fr",
          "content": [
            {
              "id": "alt-h3-1",
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 3,
              "content": "Markdown",
              "style": {
                "align": "left"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "alt-p1",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Simple and developer-friendly, but looks plain without custom styling. Great for technical writing, but lacks the presentation layer for professional documents.",
              "style": {
                "align": "left",
                "indent": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "width": "1fr",
          "content": [
            {
              "id": "alt-h3-2",
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 3,
              "content": "Notion/Proprietary Platforms",
              "style": {
                "align": "left"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "alt-p2",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Beautiful and collaborative, but your content is locked in their ecosystem. No open format means no portability, no version control, and no guarantee of long-term access.",
              "style": {
                "align": "left",
                "indent": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "gap": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "layout-alternatives-2",
      "type": "layout",
      "columns": [
        {
          "width": "1fr",
          "content": [
            {
              "id": "alt-h3-3",
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 3,
              "content": "HTML/Web Pages",
              "style": {
                "align": "left"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "alt-p3",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Flexible and ubiquitous, but too complex for document authoring. The barrier between content and presentation is blurred, making it hard for AI to extract meaning.",
              "style": {
                "align": "left",
                "indent": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "width": "1fr",
          "content": [
            {
              "id": "alt-h3-4",
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 3,
              "content": "Word Processing Files",
              "style": {
                "align": "left"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "alt-p4",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Editable but inconsistent across platforms. Complex binary or XML formats that are difficult to version control and not designed for AI consumption.",
              "style": {
                "align": "left",
                "indent": 0
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "gap": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "p-alt-conclusion",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Each of these formats excels in one dimension while failing in others. What we've been missing is a format that doesn't make us choose.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "div2",
      "type": "divider",
      "style": "solid"
    },
    {
      "id": "h2-nova",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "Enter Nova",
      "anchor": "nova",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-nova-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Nova is built on a simple but powerful idea: what if documents were semantic-first but beautiful by default?",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-nova-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "At its core, Nova is a JSON-based format that structures content into semantic blocksâ€”headings, paragraphs, tables, code, images, and more. Each block knows what it is and what it means, not just how it should look. But unlike plain Markdown or JSON, Nova includes presentation hints that ensure gorgeous rendering by default.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "callout-key",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "success",
      "title": "The Key Insight",
      "icon": "ðŸ’¡",
      "content": "Nova separates semantic structure from presentation, but provides sensible presentation defaults. This means AI can perfectly understand your content while humans see beautiful, professionally-formatted documents."
    },
    {
      "id": "h3-benefits",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "content": "Why This Matters",
      "anchor": "benefits",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "list-benefits",
      "type": "list",
      "listType": "ordered",
      "items": [
        {
          "content": "Beautiful by Default - Consistent, professional rendering without fighting CSS or layout tools"
        },
        {
          "content": "Fully Editable - Change anything at any time. No frozen artifacts, no recreation required"
        },
        {
          "content": "AI-Ready - Semantic structure means AI can perfectly understand context, relationships, and meaning"
        },
        {
          "content": "Open Format - JSON-based, human-readable, version-controllable, and MIT licensed"
        },
        {
          "content": "Modern Editing - Block-based like Notion, with live preview and intuitive UX"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "h2-real-world",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "Real-World Impact",
      "anchor": "real-world",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-real-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "The true test of any document format is how well it solves real problems. Early adopters of Nova are already seeing significant benefits:",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "h3-use-case-1",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "content": "Technical Documentation",
      "anchor": "use-case-1",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-tech-doc",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "A major tech company replaced their PDF-based API documentation with Nova. The result? Their RAG system achieved 94% accuracy in answering developer questions, up from 67% with PDFs. Developers can now search semantically, and AI assistants can provide accurate code examples based on the docs.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "quote-tech",
      "type": "quote",
      "content": "Switching to Nova cut our documentation support tickets by 40%. Developers find what they need, and when they don't, AI can help them accurately.",
      "author": "Lisa Park",
      "source": "Head of Developer Experience, TechCorp"
    },
    {
      "id": "h3-use-case-2",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "content": "Corporate Reports",
      "anchor": "use-case-2",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-reports",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "A consulting firm that produces dozens of reports monthly was spending hours converting Notion pages to PDF for clients. With Nova, they create beautiful reports directly, share them as live links, and clients can export to PDF if neededâ€”but most don't, because the Nova version is better.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "h3-use-case-3",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "content": "Academic Publishing",
      "anchor": "use-case-3",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-academic",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Researchers are using Nova for preprints and supplementary materials. The semantic structure makes it easy to extract citations, data tables, and methodology sections. One research group reported that their papers are now being cited with 30% more accuracy because AI tools can properly understand their structure.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "div3",
      "type": "divider",
      "style": "solid"
    },
    {
      "id": "h2-future",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "The Road Ahead",
      "anchor": "future",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-future-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Nova is still young, but it's growing rapidly. The core format specification is stable, with SDKs for Python and JavaScript already available. A web-based editor makes it easy to create Nova documents without writing code, and converters for Markdown and HTML are in active development.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-future-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "The real promise, though, isn't just in the format itselfâ€”it's in what becomes possible when documents are both beautiful and semantic. Imagine:",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "list-future",
      "type": "list",
      "listType": "unordered",
      "items": [
        {
          "content": "AI assistants that can accurately answer questions about any document"
        },
        {
          "content": "Search engines that understand document structure, not just keywords"
        },
        {
          "content": "Automatic translation that preserves formatting and context"
        },
        {
          "content": "Collaborative editing with the polish of published documents"
        },
        {
          "content": "Version control that actually works for documents"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "p-future-3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "These aren't distant dreamsâ€”they're natural consequences of having a document format designed for both human and machine understanding.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "callout-open",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "info",
      "title": "Open Source",
      "icon": "ðŸŒŸ",
      "content": "Nova is completely open source with an MIT license. The format specification, SDKs, renderer, and editor are all freely available. This isn't just another proprietary formatâ€”it's a community-driven standard for the AI age."
    },
    {
      "id": "h2-conclusion",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "Why This Time Is Different",
      "anchor": "conclusion",
      "style": {
        "align": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-conclusion-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "We've seen attempts to replace PDF before. Most failed because they asked users to sacrifice either beauty or functionality. Nova succeeds because it refuses that trade-off. It's beautiful like PDF, editable like modern tools, and AI-ready by design.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-conclusion-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "More importantly, Nova arrives at exactly the right moment. As AI systems become more capable, the bottleneck isn't computing powerâ€”it's getting information into formats that AI can truly understand. Nova solves that problem while making documents better for humans too.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p-conclusion-3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "The question isn't whether we need a better document format. We clearly do. The question is whether Nova can gain the adoption it needs to become that format. With its open-source foundation, clear benefits, and perfect timing, it just might.",
      "style": {
        "align": "left",
        "indent": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "quote-final",
      "type": "quote",
      "content": "Every once in a while, a new format comes along that changes how we work. Nova might be one of those moments.",
      "author": "Michael Chen",
      "source": "The Verge, 2025"
    },
